{{Race}}
'''Racialization''' refers to processes of the discursive production of [[Race (classification of human beings)|racial identities]]. It signifies the extension of dehumanizing and racial meanings to a previously racially unclassified relationship, social practice, or group.<ref name="Omi & Winant 1986">Omi & Winant 1986.</ref>
* {{cite book
|author =Omi, Michael & Howard Winant
|year =1986
|title =Racial formation in the United States : from the 1960s to the 1980s
|publisher =Routledge & Kegan Paul
|isbn =0710209703
}} To be put simply, a group of people is seen as a "race", when it was not before. 

